CARTARUM RECENTIORUM ABBREVIATIO.

TRANSUMPTUM compromiffi et decreti arbitrorum super mei-chiis inter terras Episcopi, de Aelim-teis, et terras Willelmi Balye de Amely ; quo sententia ipsa arbitrorum, Alexandri Ogilvy de eodem et Johannis Grant de Fruychquhy inest in his verbis—that the new biggit seyt be Wilyam Balye be distrowit and ly waist in tyme to cum and at he has na richt to manur nor appropir the samyn be na way of propirte; and decernis the landis of Auchquortheis to haue ficlik wyss and poffeffion of pastoring, faill and dowate casting, gethis making, wattir dracht, our all quhar fra the well of Tobirquablach lynaly discendand down to the heid of the meyr burn as the tenends of the landis of Auchquhortheis had afor the feld of Flowdone ; cum subscriptionibus, Alexander Ogssby of that ilk, Johne the Grant of Fruchquhy with my hand of the pen. At Auchindowne and Cromdell, 18 Dec. 1519.

Carta feodifirmae terrarum de Adweye, Tulchan, Calledure, Royrore, Advoky in baronia de Strathspey infra vicqcomitatum de Elgin et Fores ab Episcopo concess'a Johanni Grant de Bal- lindallaeht qui easdem prius inhabitabat, et heredibus ejus masculis, quibus deficientibus Jacobo Grant de Fruchy et heredibus ejus masculis. Reddendo 32 merens, 3 manas, 10 bullas avena- rum annuatim. Prestando tres sectas curie ad tria placita capitalia Episcopi apud Spyne. Testi- bus Jacobo Leirmonth de Dar-sy magistro hospitii Regis, David Wode de Crag rotulatore Regis, Willelmo Suthirland de Duffous, ,Iohanne Tenent, magistro Johanne Douglas, Andrea Mon- cur, Thema Dudingstoun de [ ], magistro Willelmo Grant, magistro Jacobo Wischard, Alexandro Mure. Apud Elgin, 1539.
